        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         They will not nerf anything, they are aware of it. Everyone does it in the BotBs for one thing. And on the Zeks.</P><P>The right click effect cancels out a bug in Veran't coding that they haven't fixed yet. The bug is that the server does not communicate with the client (EQ running on your box at home) until the end of the "tick". What this means is, your "average" refresh time on spells is hampered by lag. When you use a right click item you are forcing a server call from the client, so it can display what you just did. During this time it "paints" the client screen with gems reset for casting because that is the toggle that was set when the spell finished being cast.</P><P>It won't be nerfed because recast times still apply. Try casting DoTs one after another using this. No problem whatsoever; you can cast all of them fast. Now try rooting or FDing right after casting anything and using a clicky item. You get a spell recovery time not met message.</P><P>They have control over whether the gems show up (FD) and over whether the spell will work or not (recovery message). This tells me this is not an exploit and it won't be nerfed so I use it.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
